## 2. Commercial license required

Unless explicitly authorized in writing by the 7Flows maintainers, you may not:

a. operate or offer the 7Flows source code as a multi-tenant hosted service, shared control plane, or platform serving multiple customers, organizations, or workspaces

b. directly use the 7Flows source code to develop, operate, or commercialize a competing agent workflow platform, OpenClaw control plane, workflow-backed provider, or similar hosted service whose core value is substantially derived from 7Flows

c. remove, obscure, modify, or replace the 7Flows product name, logo, copyright notice, or other visible attribution displayed in the frontend when distributing or providing access to the frontend

Definitions:

- For this license, one tenant corresponds to one independent organization or workspace boundary.
- For this license, the "frontend" includes all components located in the `web/` directory when running 7Flows from source code, and any frontend build artifacts derived from that directory.

